
Overview of verb modify

The verb modify has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (17) modify -- (make less severe or harsh or extreme; "please modify this letter to make it more polite"; "he modified his views on same-gender marriage")
2. (1) modify, qualify -- (add a modifier to a constituent)
3. change, alter, modify -- (cause to change; make different; cause a transformation; "The advent of the automobile may have altered the growth pattern of the city"; "The discussion has changed my thinking about the issue")

Overview of adj modified

The adj modified has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) modified -- (changed in form or character; "their modified stand made the issue more acceptable"; "the performance of the modified aircraft was much improved")
2. (1) limited, modified -- (mediocre)
